The paper deals with the development of a toolkit for analyzing acoustic data from underwater seismic air-gun surveys. This involves the use of sound measures and data extraction techniques, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with the analysis and processing of audio signals. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.OH (Other Computer Science), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
